messages.content: Are you in grand rapids?
Hey Andy
Yo Andy!
Okay that sounds good. Yeah I arrive tomorrow!
You get back this week, right?

Yeah, that's fine. And my brother insisted on me paying $1500 for both of us. You had the flight change, but then I spent more of my brother's money after we split with you, so I say we just split the $1500: $750 each.

Hi Andy, hope everything's going well with your play and future plans for teaching. I was looking into my bank account and realised that it would be difficult to pay you all together at once since I'm low on money. Is it okay if I pay you separately? I can pay you some once I see you and the rest when I get paid from school. Let me know if that's okay with you

Yeah I'll be going alone. I will start planning tomorrow when I go to Geneva, Switzerland. I'm afraid it's going to be quite expensive so I'm thinking of buying or renting a tent and camping on my own
I guess once you go to the Alps once, you just always want to go back. That sounds pretty awesome, but make sure you know what you're doing. Are you going alone?
I'm excited yet worried
I'm thinking of spending a whole week in the Swiss Alps
Ohh I realize how difficulty that would actually be hah. I won't do it anymore because I won't have much time also. But thanks!
Cool. Yeah, that was probably good not to hike the mountain alone. And $850 is fine, if you want to do that. See you in a couple weeks. And good luck if you decide to bike Portugal
Thanks for his name by the way. And also I think you're being too generous about the cost. I'll give you $850.

Hi Andy! Right now I am in Barcelona, I arrived last night. Salzburg was so much fun and I got to hang out with some of my friends. I was going to risk my life again and hike a mountain all alone until it started to storm real bad. I took that as a sign to sit that one out.
And the slovenian hiker is Vasja LegiÅ¡a, if you want to add him on facebook

So did you make it to Salsburg alright? Where are you now? Me and Jason did one more day of hiking in the mountains. And a cute Slovenian girl offered Jason a job at one of the mountain huts, but he turned it down. I'm back in Valpo now. Jason's in Croatia. For money, I'm going to give Jason $1600 for both of us. But that includes money we spent in Croatia, so if you give me $750, that will be good, if that sounds fair. Hope everything's working out - don't fall off any more mountains
yup
It's 3.1 miles correct?
Maybe next time.. I'll run around here and make up my own trial
Haha
yeah. right up the road at the park by meridian and highway 6. you could come and try to sneak in
Is it a 5K?
go for it
But really, Good luck. I think I might go for a run as well around that time just to pretend. I'll be there in spirit! Ha
Like a bullet he was
Yeah that man can gun it out in the field
And don't forget Thomas "The Tank" Jefferson
Yeah.. among the greatest but never as good as Washington
I'll remember that. No one could run like old Woody
Remember what good old Woody would say.. run like there's no tomorrow
Nice, good luck!
leaving in a few minutes. race is at 9
Did you run already?
Hey!
Hey!
Haha that's fine
Hi. I don't know how to do one of those super hero things
